1️⃣ Subpixel Edge Detection

Goal: Increase diameter precision beyond 1-pixel resolution.

Required changes:

Replace binary edge detection with grayscale edge analysis.

For each scanline:

Detect intensity transition using gradient (Sobel) OR

Detect threshold crossing between adjacent pixels.

Linearly interpolate edge position between two pixels.

Compute diameter using interpolated (float) positions.

Keep averaging across scanlines.

Expected result:
Precision improved from ±1 px to ~±0.1 px.

2️⃣ Automatic MM_PER_PIXEL Calibration

Goal: Remove hardcoded pixel-to-mm scale.

Required changes:

Add calibration mode.

Detect object of known diameter (or known-width rectangle).

Measure its pixel diameter using same algorithm.

Compute:

MM_PER_PIXEL = known_mm / measured_pixels


Store value (optionally save to file).

Use updated scale for live measurements.

Optional upgrade:

Recalculate if resolution changes.

3️⃣ Performance Optimization

Goal: Improve FPS and CPU efficiency.

Required changes:

Convert to grayscale AFTER cropping ROIs (not full frame).

Reduce frame resolution if full width not needed.

Replace Python scanline loop with vectorized NumPy logic.

Disable or optionally toggle debug windows (imshow).

Reduce NUM_SCANLINES if performance limited.

Expected result:

Higher FPS

Lower CPU load

More stable real-time behavior

4️⃣ Ovality Detection

Goal: Detect non-circular filament shape.

Option A (Simple):

Add horizontal scanlines.

Compute horizontal diameter.

Compare with vertical diameter.

Compute:

ovality = (D_max - D_min) / D_avg


Option B (More Accurate):

Detect binary contour in ROI.

Fit ellipse to contour.

Extract:

Major axis

Minor axis

Rotation angle

Compute ovality from axes.

Expected result:

Detect deformation even if average diameter is correct.

5️⃣ Perspective / Optical Correction (Optional Advanced)

Goal: Remove distortion from camera angle.

Required changes:

Use calibration grid.

Compute homography matrix.

Warp frame to top-down view before measurement.

Recalculate MM_PER_PIXEL after warping.

🎯 Final Upgrade Priority (Recommended Order)

Subpixel edge detection (biggest accuracy gain)

Auto calibration

Ovality detection

Performance optimization

Perspective correction (only if needed)

